<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Raglan cuts deficit to Pounds 1.6m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PRE-TAX losses for the year to end-March at Raglan Property Trust were
Pounds 1.6m, against Pounds 4m at the previous year-end. Turnover increased
from Pounds 7.06m to Pounds 9.49m.
The pre-tax improvement was achieved after a reduced charge of Pounds
960,000 (Pounds 3.62m) for property write-offs.
Losses per share were cut to 0.9p (2p).
The directors said the company was continuing to reduce its indebtedness and
to unwind outstanding development liabilities initiated in the late-1980s.
Litigation with Security Pacific National Bank had been settled at a figure
significantly below the claim and had been provided for in the 1991
accounts, they added.
Having considerably reduced debt, the directors are addressing the task of
restructuring the group's balance sheet.
Discussions are under way with its three leading banks on a capital
restructuring in order that negotiations with another party could be
pursued.
</TEXT>
