FT  06 OCT 92 / Scientist warns on passive smoking
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A LEADING cancer researcher urged employers yesterday to ensure staff did
not have to suffer passive smoking at work, Lisa Wood writes.
Sir Richard Doll, a consultant with the Imperial Cancer Research Fund, said
that about 0.5 per cent to 1 per cent of all cancers were caused by tobacco
smoke at work.
Urging companies to support next week's European Week Against Cancer, Sir
Richard said, 'People have a right to work in a smoke-free area, and there
is no reason why they should have other peoples' carcinogens passed on to
them.
