The speech was so unclear she was not sure 'where he comes out' because
'words seem to be strewn around to attract every view.'
There had been no 'glaring omission' on worker adjustment aid, because Mr
Bush had announced 'a Dollars 10bn (Pounds 5.6bn) five-year programme for
workers displaced by the pact. She denied Mexican truckers could drive in
the US without meeting its safety standards, that foods with pesticide
residues would be allowed into the US, or that environmental safeguards were
insufficient.
