An El Al 747 cargo aircraft exploded in mid-air last night over the
Amsterdam suburb of Weesp. A block of flats was ablaze after being hit by
falling wreckage which was said to be scattered over a wide area. The Tel
Aviv-bound Boeing had just taken off from Amsterdam's Schiphol airport and
tried to turn back before it exploded. The aircraft's crew of four were
reported killed.
