<TEXT>
NFC, the transport and distribution group, has issued Pounds 82.5m of
convertible bonds to refinance part of its bank debt, writes Richard Waters.
The bonds are convertible from March 1998 at 300p. The premium, 18.6 per
cent over the share price of 253p yesterday, is marginally higher than the
