reports from Moscow.
State enterprises only have to sell half their hard currency earnings to the
state - at the going market rate - at present.
Mr Sergei Glazyev, the first deputy foreign trade minister, said firms had
taken advantage of this ruling to stash away Dollars 3.5bn in foreign bank
accounts.
The rouble fell to a record low of 309 to the dollar on Thursday in Moscow
trading.
